    {
      "page_number": 113,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "section_title",
          "arabic": "[3-3] اختبار التزايد والتناقص للدالة باستخدام المشتقة الأولى",
          "english": "[3-3] The First Derivative Test For Increasing And Decreasing of a Function"
        },
        {
          "type": "subsection_title",
          "arabic": "[3-3-1] نتيجة",
          "english": "[3-3-1] Result"
        },
        {
          "type": "theorem",
          "arabic": "إن من النتائج المهمة لمبرهنة القيمة المتوسطة هي النتيجة الاتية: لتكن $f$ مستمرة في الفترة المغلقة $[a,b]$ وقابلة للاشتقاق في الفترة المفتوحة $(a,b)$ فإذا كانت",
          "english": "One of the important results of the Mean Value Theorem is the following: Let $f$ be continuous on the closed interval $[a,b]$ and differentiable on the open interval $(a,b)$.",
          "conditions": [
            {
              "number": 1,
              "description": "If $f'(x) > 0, \\forall x \\in (a,b)$",
              "conclusion_arabic": "$f$ متزايدة",
              "conclusion_english": "$f$ is Increasing"
            },
            {
              "number": 2,
              "description": "If $f'(x) < 0, \\forall x \\in (a,b)$",
              "conclusion_arabic": "$f$ متناقصة",
              "conclusion_english": "$f$ is Decreasing"
            }
          ],
          "note_arabic": "أما بقية الحالات فسوف لا نتطرق لها في هذه المرحلة.",
          "note_english": "The remaining cases will not be discussed at this stage."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "number": 1,
          "arabic_title": "لتكن $y = f(x) = x^2$. جد مناطق التزايد والتناقص",
          "english_title": "Let $y = f(x) = x^2$. Find the intervals of increasing and decreasing.",
          "solution": [
            {
              "step": "Function and its first derivative:",
              "equation": "$y = f(x) = x^2 \\implies y' = 2x$"
            },
            {
              "step": "Find critical points by setting $y' = 0$:",
              "equation": "$y' = 0 \\implies 2x = 0 \\implies x = 0$"
            },
            {
              "step": "Sign analysis of $y' = 2x$ (diagram shown in image):",
              "diagram_description": "A number line with 0 marked, showing $y'$ is negative to the left of 0 and positive to the right of 0. An arrow to the left indicates decreasing, an arrow to the right indicates increasing."
            },
            {
              "step": "Conclusion for increasing intervals:",
              "equation": "$\\therefore f'(x) > 0, \\forall x > 0 \\implies f$ متزايدة في $\{x: x > 0\}$"
            },
            {
              "step": "Conclusion for decreasing intervals:",
              "equation": "$\\therefore f'(x) < 0, \\forall x < 0 \\implies f$ متناقصة في $\{x: x < 0\}$"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_number": 114,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "example",
          "number": 2,
          "arabic_title": "جد مناطق التزايد والتناقص لكل من الدالتين الاتيتين:",
          "english_title": "Find the intervals of increasing and decreasing for each of the following functions:",
          "problems": [
            {
              "id": "a",
              "function": "$f(x) = 9x + 3x^2 - x^3$",
              "solution": [
                {
                  "step": "First derivative:",
                  "equation": "$f(x) = 9x + 3x^2 - x^3 \\implies f'(x) = 9 + 6x - 3x^2$"
                },
                {
                  "step": "Set $f'(x) = 0$ to find critical points:",
                  "equation": "$0 = 9 + 6x - 3x^2$"
                },
                {
                  "step": "Factor (divide by -3):",
                  "equation": "$0 = x^2 - 2x - 3$"
                },
                {
                  "step": "Solve for x:",
                  "equation": "$0 = (x-3)(x+1) \\implies x=3, x=-1$"
                },
                {
                  "step": "Test the sign of the first derivative on the number line:",
                  "diagram_description": "A number line with critical points -1 and 3. Sign of $f'(x)$ is negative for $x<-1$, positive for $-1<x<3$, and negative for $x>3$. Arrows indicate decreasing, then increasing, then decreasing."
                },
                {
                  "step": "Conclusion for decreasing intervals:",
                  "equation": "$f$ متناقصة في $\{x: x < -1\\} \\cup \\{x: x > 3\\}$"
                },
                {
                  "step": "Conclusion for increasing intervals:",
                  "equation": "$f$ متزايدة في الفترة المفتوحة $(-1, 3)$"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "b",
              "function": "$f(x) = \\sqrt[3]{x^2}$",
              "solution": [
                {
                  "step": "First derivative:",
                  "equation": "$f(x) = x^{\\\\frac{2}{3}} \\implies f'(x) = \\frac{2}{3}x^{-\\\\frac{1}{3}} = \\frac{2}{3\\sqrt[3]{x}}$"
                },
                {
                  "step": "Critical points (where $f'(x)=0$ or $f'(x)$ is undefined):",
                  "equation": "$f'(x)$ غير معرفه اذا كانت $x=0$, واي $x=0$ عدد حرج"
                },
                {
                  "step": "Test the sign of the first derivative on the number line:",
                  "diagram_description": "A number line with critical point 0. Sign of $f'(x)$ is negative for $x<0$ and positive for $x>0$. Arrows indicate decreasing, then increasing."
                },
                {
                  "step": "Conclusion for increasing intervals:",
                  "equation": "$f$ متزايدة في $\{x: x > 0\\}$"
                },
                {
                  "step": "Conclusion for decreasing intervals:",
                  "equation": "$f$ متناقصة في $\{x: x < 0\\}$"
                },
                {
                  "step": "Graph:",
                  "graph_description": "A graph of $y=x^{\\\\frac{2}{3}}$ showing a cusp at the origin, decreasing for $x<0$ and increasing for $x>0$."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_number": 115,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "section_title",
          "arabic": "[3-4] النهاية العظمى والنهاية الصغرى المحلية",
          "english": "[3-4] Local Maximum and Local Minimum"
        },
        {
          "type": "explanation",
          "arabic": "لاحظ في الشكل أدناه أن الدالة $(x)f$ متزايدة على الفترة $(a,c)$ لأن $(x)f'>0$ ومتناقصة على الفترة $(c,d)$ لأن $(x)f'<0$ ثم تتزايد في الفترة $(d,b)$ . كما أن $f'(c)=0$ عند كل من $c=x, x=d$. تسمى نقطة $(c,f(c))$ نقطة نهاية عظمى محلية وان $(c)f$ هي النهاية العظمى المحلية بينما النقطة $(d,f(d))$ نقطة نهاية صغرى محلية وان $(d)f$ هي النهاية الصغرى المحلية (Local Minimum).",
          "english": "Observe from the figure below that the function $f(x)$ is increasing on the interval $(a,c)$ because $f'(x)>0$, and decreasing on the interval $(c,d)$ because $f'(x)<0$. Then it increases again in the interval $(d,b)$. Also, $f'(c)=0$ at $x=c$ and $x=d$. The point $(c,f(c))$ is called a local maximum point, and $f(c)$ is the local maximum. The point $(d,f(d))$ is called a local minimum point, and $f(d)$ is the local minimum (Local Minimum).",
          "diagram_description": "A number line showing the sign of $f'(x)$. $f'(x)>0$ in $(a,c)$, $f'(x)<0$ in $(c,d)$, and $f'(x)>0$ in $(d,b)$. Points $c$ and $d$ are critical points."
        },
        {
          "type": "definition",
          "number": "3-4-1",
          "arabic_title": "تعريف",
          "english_title": "Definition",
          "body_arabic": "لتكن $f$ دالة مستمرة على الفترة $[a,b]$ وقابلة للاشتقاق عند $x=c$ التي تنتمي الى الفترة المفتوحة $(a,b)$ فإذا كانت:",
          "body_english": "Let $f$ be a function continuous on the closed interval $[a,b]$ and differentiable at $x=c$ which belongs to the open interval $(a,b)$. If:",
          "cases": [
            {
              "number": 1,
              "conditions_arabic": "1) $f'(x) < 0, \\forall x \\in (c,b)$ and $f'(x) > 0, \\forall x \\in (a,c)$ and $f'(c) = 0$",
              "conditions_english": "1) $f'(x) < 0, \\forall x \\in (c,b)$ and $f'(x) > 0, \\forall x \\in (a,c)$ and $f'(c) = 0$",
              "conclusion_arabic": "فإن $f(c)$ نهاية عظمى محلية",
              "conclusion_english": "Then $f(c)$ is a local maximum.",
              "diagram_description": "Number line showing $f'(x)$ positive to the left of $c$ and negative to the right of $c$."
            },
            {
              "number": 2,
              "conditions_arabic": "2) $f'(x) > 0, \\forall x \\in (c,b)$ and $f'(x) < 0, \\forall x \\in (a,c)$ and $f'(c) = 0$",
              "conditions_english": "2) $f'(x) > 0, \\forall x \\in (c,b)$ and $f'(x) < 0, \\forall x \\in (a,c)$ and $f'(c) = 0$",
              "conclusion_arabic": "فإن $f(c)$ نهاية صغرى محلية",
              "conclusion_english": "Then $f(c)$ is a local minimum.",
              "diagram_description": "Number line showing $f'(x)$ negative to the left of $c$ and positive to the right of $c$."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_number": 116,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "note",
          "arabic_title": "ملاحظة",
          "english_title": "Note",
          "body_arabic": "لكي نختبر القيمة العظمى والصغرى المحلية للدالة $f$ بواسطة المشتقة الأولى للدالة $f$ نتبع الخطوات الاتية:",
          "body_english": "To test for local maximum and minimum values of a function $f$ using the first derivative test, we follow these steps:",
          "steps": [
            {
              "number": 1,
              "arabic": "جد الاعداد الحرجة وذلك بحل المعادلة $f'(x)=0$ وليكن $x=x_1$ هو أحد هذه الأعداد الحرجة.",
              "english": "Find the critical numbers by solving the equation $f'(x)=0$. Let $x=x_1$ be one of these critical numbers."
            },
            {
              "number": 2,
              "arabic": "نختبر إشارة $f'(x)$ بجوار $x=x_1$. فإذا كانت إشارة $f'(x)$ موجبة $x < x_1$ وسالبة $x > x_1$",
              "english": "Test the sign of $f'(x)$ around $x=x_1$. If the sign of $f'(x)$ is positive for $x < x_1$ and negative for $x > x_1$:",
              "sub_step_1": {
                "arabic": "فهذا يعني أن $(x_1, f(x_1))$ نقطة نهاية عظمى محلية.",
                "english": "This means that $(x_1, f(x_1))$ is a local maximum point."
              },
              "sub_step_2": {
                "arabic": "أما إذا كانت إشارة $f'(x)$ سالبة $x < x_1$ وموجبة $x > x_1$",
                "english": "If the sign of $f'(x)$ is negative for $x < x_1$ and positive for $x > x_1$:",
                "sub_sub_step_1": {
                  "arabic": "فهذا يعني أن $(x_1, f(x_1))$ نقطة نهاية صغرى محلية.",
                  "english": "This means that $(x_1, f(x_1))$ is a local minimum point."
                }
              },
              "sub_step_3": {
                "arabic": "أما إذا كانت إشارة $f'(x)$ لا تتغير قبل وبعد $x_1$ فلا يكون للدالة نقطة نهاية عظمى ولا صغرى عند هذه النقطة.",
                "english": "However, if the sign of $f'(x)$ does not change before and after $x_1$, then the function has neither a local maximum nor a local minimum at this point."
              }
            }
          ],
          "diagrams": [
            {
              "description_arabic": "تغير إشارة $f'(x)$ من موجب إلى سالب عند $x_1$ (نهاية عظمى محلية)",
              "description_english": "Sign of $f'(x)$ changes from positive to negative at $x_1$ (Local maximum point)",
              "graph_type": "local_maximum_diagram"
